<paragraph id="3340217A403D5F16FCD4FE074A2B3B70" blockId="42.[806,1422,396,786]" pageId="42" pageNumber="309">
<emphasis id="018BFD68403D5F16FCD4FE074C8D39C0" box="[806,1001,397,418]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="309">Taxonomic notes:</emphasis>
The transverse prolegs only developed on abdominal segments 1–5 suggest this species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9403D5F16FC47FE404B5F39BD" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[949,1083,458,479]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="309" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puyarum">
<emphasis id="018BFD68403D5F16FC47FE404B5F39BD" box="[949,1083,458,479]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="309">C. puyarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the thorax is not as wide as the abdomen and there are no long fleshy projections bearing sensilla on any of the segments. It is also similar to 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9403D5F16FC6CFDAC4C983A59" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[926,1020,550,571]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="309" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yowoi">
<emphasis id="018BFD68403D5F16FC6CFDAC4C983A59" box="[926,1020,550,571]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="309">C. yowoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but has a wider than deep, tapering posterior breathing tube. In 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9403D5F16FB7DFDCF4B893A38" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[1167,1261,581,602]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="309" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yowoi">
<emphasis id="018BFD68403D5F16FB7DFDCF4B893A38" box="[1167,1261,581,602]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="309">C. yowoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the breathing tube is as wide as deep and is parallel sided. The early stages of 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9403D5F16FC6CFD084B423AF5" baseAuthorityName="Hull" baseAuthorityYear="1934" box="[926,1062,642,663]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="309" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="emeralda">
<emphasis id="018BFD68403D5F16FC6CFD084B423AF5" box="[926,1062,642,663]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="309">C. emeralda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are also easily distinguished from all other bromeliad 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9403D5F16FBBDFD2A4BB73AD7" authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1846" box="[1103,1235,672,693]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="309" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="018BFD68403D5F16FBBDFD2A4BB73AD7" box="[1103,1235,672,693]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="309">Copestylum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
early stages by the well-developed lappet 1, which is either as long as or longer than lappet 2, and the posterior breathing tube, which is broader than the pupal spiracles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3340217A403D5F16FCD4FCA04BD03B1C" blockId="42.[806,1422,810,894]" pageId="42" pageNumber="309">
<emphasis id="018BFD68403D5F16FCD4FCA04CE53B5D" box="[806,897,810,831]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="309">Biology:</emphasis>
Reared from larvae found among the decaying outer leaves of a bromeliad (
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9403D5F16FB59FCC34A233B3D" box="[1195,1351,841,863]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="42" pageNumber="309" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Bromeliaceae</taxonomicName>
) on a branch of a cut tree in 
<collectingCountry id="4BE861EA403D5F16FBC3FCE24BD43B1C" box="[1073,1200,872,894]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="42" pageNumber="309">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
